sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant FD as Finance Director
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment and expedited path
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Co., Clean History?)

    alt Low-Risk (Score >750 + Verified + No Issues) — Expedited Path
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved (bypass FD review)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk — Standard Approval Path
        F->>FD: Escalate for Finance Director approval
        FD-->>F: Approval decision (24h SLA)
        F-->>S: Approval forwarded
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (standard)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a Finance Director (FD) participant and a risk assessment step after the credit check. An alt/else block now splits the flow: low-risk customers (credit score >750, verified company status, clean payment history) are auto-approved and proceed directly to expedited account provisioning, while high-risk customers are escalated to the Finance Director for manual approval before provisioning continues through the standard path.